One Christian song that describes the sentiment or situation in this passage is "Great Is Thy Faithfulness" by Thomas Chisholm and William M. Runyan. 

The song speaks of God's faithfulness and provision, even in the wilderness. The lyrics affirm God's ability to provide for His people, just as the Israelites questioned in Psalm 78:17-20. The song also emphasizes God's guidance and protection, as mentioned in Psalm 78:52-55.

Here are some lines from "Great Is Thy Faithfulness" that relate to the passage:

"Great is thy faithfulness, O God my Father,
There is no shadow of turning with thee;
Thou changest not, thy compassions, they fail not;
As thou hast been, thou forever wilt be.

Great is thy faithfulness! Great is thy faithfulness!
Morning by morning new mercies I see;
All I have needed thy hand hath provided;
Great is thy faithfulness, Lord, unto me."

These lines acknowledge God's unchanging faithfulness and His continuous provision, just as the Psalm highlights the Israelites' doubts about God's ability to provide in the wilderness.
